Parents are stupid. But siblings aren't too much better. My Dad found me on the computer at like 1am (go figure I forget he is still asleep downstairs) and he told me to get my butt upstairs and leave the computer on. My dad did what he has always threatened to do. Change the password on the computer. My life is ridiculous. RIDICULOUS. Yes, ridiculous. I'm going crazy. Why can't I be one of the graduating senoirs who are going off to college and leaving their family at home? Its not fair. Can't wait for college. No parents. And my older sister keeps acting like my mom. I'm good with only one mom, thanks... Harry Potter was fun. Half of it I spent talking to sarah about what was wrong with the movie :P good times...

I am Galadriel, Queen of Lothlorien. I was given Nenya, the Ring of Adamant, but I remained untouched by the Shadow. I gave shelter, gifts and advice to the Fellowship, but I turned green while they were around. My bad. In the movie, I'm played by Cate Blanchett.

Life is taking a trip down a public, much used, Walmart toilet. I can't even talk to a person without the smallest person. People are giving me crap for everything I say and I'm becoming a friggin' recluse. And when I'm not a recluse people already have plans and I end up going out with my sister and her friends. I'm just mad at myself, I suppose, for being a last minute beast!

Troy was good, but Eric Bana is THE hottest guy in that movie. *swoons*

I love vacation...I have absoutly nothing to do (hence, me writing in my journal-lol) I haven't talked to anyone in forever. I feel so disconnected. I also feel like a hampster has been eating my brain (yes, I know, good mental picture there) since january. I just need time to get away from everything and everyone thats been bothering me. 

I can't wait till monday. Might be going to the Boston MArathon after practice. Teehee. Probably the only exciting thing I'll do all vacation *gasp*- the excitment-lol :D

Haven't written in this beast for awhile-hehe. FRIDAY ROCKED! Best field trip in the history in my life! Sure, there was that field trip to the fire station in foxboro when I was like 6, but that doesn't compare! Emil and I hung around Chris and Jess and it twas ze best day ever. Was choking down my lunch because I was laughing so hard. My brothr just said he isn't going to be home on his birthday :o!!! He'll probably be too busy getting drunk anyway to remember us :(. My sister is gone for her Spring Break, though she is home all the time. Down in Maryland doing who knows what :(. Then my brother is leaving today leaving ME with Jenn and Jeff (kill me now). You say something wrong to one of them and they both jump on your back. I hope my friends get undepressed soon because I hate seeing it :(

So tired *in general* of school. School needs to go away- it needs to die. Maybe not DIE exactly but just go away...forever. Hehe. School wasn't bad itself. "It's me, not you."- thats me talking to school. (NOT JOKING!) The thing is being a zombie and being wicked tired for like two weeks- midterms last week- is taking its toll on me and it needs to stop. I'm getting real sleep tongiht and no one is going to stop me. State coaches meet this weekend and I'm running the 2 mile. Nervous already. Another factor of my tiredishishness! It needs to stop, it really does. But my friends are awesome. That much can be said. lol- Sarah's Critique

ONE MORE ANNOUNCEMENT!!!

feehan- 1 of 7 or 8 or 9 *so many people were telling me different friggin numbers!* schools actually open. totally stupid. I only did review in like two classes. So fucking stupid. It was so stupid. I just wanted to be at home with my family but nooooooooooo i had to go to school and do nothing. WELL SCREW YOU! Stupid bishop fenwick or however the fuck you spell it.

I have done ZERO homework tonight. I don't want to. Supposedly we'll have school tomorrow- can't wait to walk to art in -35 degree wind chill in my skirt *woohoo*. If you couldn't detect the sarcasm there there was a whole shit load of it. I have so much to do but i am not doing any of it. School was okay. Lunch was wicked funny though. That game was disturbing, Emily and Sarah, disturbing yet fun o.o Track is frustrating and I can't wait to get back into shape. Getting tired of pretending to be a patient person -.-

Or maybe turn into an inanimate object. Screw life in general. Screw it.

If you're still mad at me, try not to be. My life is so fucked up. I need my friends.

Okay...summer is going by really quickly and it needs to slow down! Its already been more than two weeks! I need to do more stuff. POTC!!!!! Oh boy I'm so excited. Oh I'm sorry did i say excited, i meant Xcited. My sister will probably be coming home for the end of the summer but there are things in that situation that i probably shouldnt write down here, in some online journal. But that also means my brother will be leaving for UCONN. Not very happy times, i can tell you. I think my biggest problem is I hate change. I once changed the bedspread in my room and it felt weird...I don't know, i am just weird in the change area... Cannot wait until potc comes out only more days!!!

Yeah, yesterday was the 4th (happy Birthday America! lol) and a bunch of my cousins came over. It was fun we ate and went in the pool. That was pretty much our day. I was so freaking tired at the end of it i went straight to bed (after watching the boston pops o' course) and went to bed and klonked out. Well its another day closer to POTC I'm so Xcited! LOL! I need to calm down!

Woke up this morning at 5:45 am!!! Insane, yes I know! I woke up and it was weird I put my head back down and I wasn't tired @ all!! I was incredibly hungry too. I was even up before my dad. My parents were wondering if it was really me and not some imposter. lol. Maybe before i go to bed ill read some hp. or should I say some MORE harry potter. It'll get me depressed but at least ill be depressed for a reason and itll not just be a random mood swingedything.
